node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.title: How Porsche went from sports cars to SUVs ... and EVs

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.title: This 27-year-old spent $100,000 renovating his $560,000 condo in Hawaii

⁠⁠
After years of researching how to moderate kids’ screen time, @CNBCMakeIt contributor ⁠⁠

⁠⁠
Visit the link in bio for another common screen-time statement parents shouldn’t use — along with examples of what to say instead.

node.text:
🚨 BREAKING. 🚨⁠
⁠
New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo said Tuesday he will resign in two weeks because of a sexual harassment scandal that has crippled his administration.⁠
⁠
Cuomo’s shock announcement came after his lawyer again flatly denied claims that he had sexually harassed anyone. Lt. Gov. Kathy Hochul will replace Cuomo as governor, becoming the Empire State’s first female chief executive.⁠
⁠
This story is developing. Get full updates at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people sitting and text that says 'AMC says it will acce bitcoin as payment for movie tickets by year-end NKU CNBC'.

node.text:
Bitcoin is heading to the big screen. 🎥⁠
⁠
AMC Entertainment said Monday it will start accepting bitcoin as payment for movie tickets and concessions if purchased online at all of its U.S. theaters.  CEO Adam Aron said during an earnings call that the movie theater chain will have the IT systems in place to take the cryptocurrency as payment by the end of 2021.⁠
⁠
Get full details on the company's announcement at the link in bio.

node.text:
The pandemic is not coming to an end soon — given that only a small proportion of the world population has been vaccinated against Covid-19, a well-known epidemiologist said.⁠
⁠
Dr. Larry Brilliant, an epidemiologist who was part of the WHO's team that helped eradicate smallpox, said the delta variant is “maybe the most contagious virus” ever.⁠
⁠
But what does Brilliant say the good news is? Find out at the link in bio.

⁠
And the company revealed that about 70% of its equity portfolio was concentrated in just four names. 👀⁠
⁠
To take a look at these high-conviction bets from the Oracle of Omaha, visit the link in bio. (Check out CNBC Pro for free for 7 days!)

node.text:
Employers in the U.S. face an interesting challenge ahead – how to fill nearly 10 million job openings with about a million fewer workers than there are positions available. 😮⁠
⁠
How successful they are will go a long way in determining whether the recent outsized job gains can continue.⁠
⁠
Details on the variety of techniques that employers have been using to try to entice people back to work (including signing bonuses, etc.) at the link in bio.

node.text:
“It’s scary what’s happening in Florida,” said an attorney for Norwegian Cruise Line.⁠
⁠
Norwegian Cruise Line said Sunday that a federal judge ruled to temporarily halt enforcement of a Florida law prohibiting businesses from requiring customers to show proof of vaccination. U.S. District Judge Kathleen Williams granted the preliminary injunction, allowing Norwegian to require vaccine documentation from customers while the case heads to trial. The Norwegian Gem is scheduled to depart Miami on Aug. 15. It is the cruise line’s first trip from the state since the pandemic halted the cruise industry’s operations more than a year ago.⁠
⁠
How much have Covid infection levels risen in Florida in the past week? Link in bio to find out.

node.text:
You may have been intent on leaving your job, and then your current employer makes a counteroffer.⁠
⁠
Whether or not to accept depends on your situation.⁠
⁠
“Ultimately, the answer is going to be: What does your career need next? What options on the table are going to get you there? Are you going to fulfill the needs that you have?” said Alison Sullivan, Glassdoor career trends expert.⁠
⁠
Details on why nearly 40% of senior executive and human resource leaders believe accepting a counteroffer from a current employer can adversely impact your career at the link in bio. (In partnership with @acorns #investinyou) ⁠

node.text:
While it’s “healthy and perfectly human to have a little bit of doubt,” it’s important not to let these fears get in the way of pursuing a dream, says Virgin Group founder Richard Branson.⁠
⁠
“What I’ve learnt throughout my life is that every success is built upon a thousand failures (or ‘opportunities to learn,’ as I like to think of them),” Branson said. ⁠
⁠
Details on what Branson does whenever "doubt creeps in" at the link in bio. ⁠(With @CNBCMakeit)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Americans say they need to have $500,000 in savings to feel financially secure, survey finds CNBC'.

node.text:
How much money do you think you need to feel financial secure?⁠
⁠
When asked how much money they need to have saved to consider themselves financially healthy, Americans put the number at $516,433, on average, according to a new report by financial services company Personal Capital. ⁠
⁠
About 20% said they would need more than $1,000,000.Why $500,000? Link in Bio⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Millions of student loan borrowers don't have a diploma to show for their debt'.

node.text:
Do you have student debt?⁠
⁠
U.S. student debt has increased by more than 100% over the past 10 years and today, 44.7 million borrowers collectively owe more than $1.7 trillion dollars in student debt. ⁠
⁠
But not all of these borrowers have a degree to show for their debts. According to the National Center for Education Statistics, just 41% of first-time full-time college students earn a bachelor’s degree in four years, and only 59% earn a bachelor’s in six years.⁠
⁠
Details on why one expert says student loan borrowers without a degree constitutes “the number one crisis in student lending" at the link in bio. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.text:
Have you traded crypto recently?⁠
⁠
More than 1 in 10 Americans invested in cryptocurrency over the past year, according to a survey published by the University of Chicago, a sign of the popularity of digital currencies like bitcoin and ethereum. Specifically, 13% bought or traded crypto in the past 12 months — by comparison, 24% of Americans invested in stocks over the same time period, according to the survey.⁠
⁠
How much of your portfolio do financial advisors say you should allocate to crypto? Link in bio. ⁠
